	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002385_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<!--Hand 01 55 top left--><!--hand 02 63002 top right--><!--headed notepaper-->
<lb/><p rend="right">50, ALBEMARLE <choice><abbr><hi rend="smallcaps">S<hi rend="sup">T</hi></hi></abbr><expan>Street</expan></choice></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">W.</p><!--end of headed paper-->
<lb/><p rend="right">7 August 1865</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear Oswell</p>
<lb/><p>I send you a 
<lb/>proof of what I 
<lb/>mean as a sort 
<lb/>of answer to <unclear cert="medium">Lacenda</unclear>
<lb/>It is to be a postscript 
<lb/>to the Preface 
<lb/>&amp; M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>  Murray 
<lb/>thinks I have put 
<lb/>it pretty well 
<lb/>return it with 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002385_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>corrections as soon 
<lb/>as you can. I 
<lb/>enclose the King 
<lb/>of Portugal's speech 
<lb/>and mean to add 
<lb/>a sentence to the 
<lb/>effect that I 
<lb/>have seen it &amp; 
<lb/>my opinion 
<lb/>remains 
<w>un-<lb break="no"/>altered.</w> I have 
<lb/>this moment 
<lb/>arrived from 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002385_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/>Newstead - (Monday 
<lb/>noon) with M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> &amp; 
<lb/>M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi> Webb. They 
<lb/>come for advice</p>
<lb/><p>My kind love 
<lb/>to M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi> Oswell &amp; 
<lb/>her chicks. I 
<lb/>send this to 
<lb/>Forest House 
<lb/>in case you are 
<lb/>still there. Agnes 
<lb/>&amp; I propose to 
<lb/>start this day 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002385_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<lb/>week for Paris 
<lb/>13<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> I to be at 
<lb/>Marseilles on 20<hi rend="sup">th</hi></p>
<lb/><p>Ever Affectionately 
<lb/>Yours</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p><!--MH Hand 03 written at right angles-->
<lb/><p><unclear cert="low">protected</unclear> with the 
<lb/>view of preventing</p>
			
</div>
